%% Data Flow Diagram for rhods-operator
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy) 443/TCP
    participant AuthFilter as EnvoyFilter<br/>(ext_authz)
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Backend as Backend Service<br/>(via HTTPRoute)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 1: External User Request via Gateway API

    User->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>Gateway: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS reencrypt
    Gateway->>AuthFilter: Intercept request
    AuthFilter->>AuthProxy: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS (service-ca)<br/>Cookie: _oauth2_proxy
    AuthProxy->>OAuth: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>OAuth2/OIDC
    OAuth-->>AuthProxy: Access Token
    AuthProxy-->>AuthFilter: Auth OK + Token
    AuthFilter->>AuthFilter: Lua filter: strip cookies,<br/>convert to Bearer token
    AuthFilter->>Backend: HTTPS/443 or 8443<br/>TLS (DestinationRule)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Backend-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Component Deployment

    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller<br/>(e.g., Dashboard)

    User->>K8sAPI: Create/Update DSC CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>DSCCtrl: Watch event
    DSCCtrl->>CompCtrl: Reconcile component<br/>(in-process)
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Apply Kustomize manifests<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>CompCtrl: Resources created/updated

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Monitoring Data Collection

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)

    Prometheus->>AuthProxy: Scrape metrics<br/>HTTP/9000 plaintext<br/>(NetworkPolicy allows)
    AuthProxy-->>Prometheus: Metrics response
    Prometheus->>DSCCtrl: Scrape metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 plaintext
    DSCCtrl-->>Prometheus: Metrics response
